<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="100" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis betulae" order="Diaporthales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="betulae">Melanconis betulae</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula albosinensis" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albosinensis">Betula albosinensis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" url="http://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-016-1163-2" year="2016">Fan et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. betulae" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="betulae">M. betulae</taxonomicName>
is characterised by ovoid, olive-brown, aseptate alpha conidia, which are different from other 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
species but similar to the type species 
<taxonomicName genus="Ms." lsidName="Ms. stilbostoma" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="stilbostoma">Ms. stilbostoma</taxonomicName>
. However, it can be distinguished by the smaller length of its alpha conidia (10 vs.&gt; 12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and sequence data.
</paragraph>
